## Public Member Functions

### flush() {#a2cb494b6794b875a17f4b0ddb5f858af}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="void llvm::symbolize::MarkupParser::flush ()">
Inform the parser of that the input stream has ended.

This allows the parser to finish any deferred processing (e.g., an in-progress multi-line element) and may cause <a href="#a1eaa76c1f1e142ff478fe1ac0196cab9">nextNode()</a> to return additional nodes.

### parseLine() {#af65477d093fd230a78c34132fd3a6546}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::symbolize::MarkupParser::parseLine (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Line)</>}>
Parses an individual <code>Line</code> of input.

Nodes from the previous <a href="#af65477d093fd230a78c34132fd3a6546">parseLine()</a> call that haven&#39;t yet been extracted by <a href="#a1eaa76c1f1e142ff478fe1ac0196cab9">nextNode()</a> are discarded. The nodes returned by <a href="#a1eaa76c1f1e142ff478fe1ac0196cab9">nextNode()</a> may reference the input string, so it must be retained by the caller until the last use.

Note that some elements may span multiple lines. If a line ends with the start of one of these elements, then no nodes will be produced until the either the end or something that cannot be part of an element is encountered. This may only occur after multiple calls to <a href="#af65477d093fd230a78c34132fd3a6546">parseLine()</a>, corresponding to the lines of the multi-line element.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/symbolize/markup-h/#l00067">67</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/symbolize/markup-h">Markup.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/symbolize/markup-cpp/#l00037">37</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/symbolize/markup-cpp">Markup.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
